 \]
Suppose that the initial distribution is $ p_i = \frac{1}{4} $ for $ i=0,1,2,3 $. Given that $ \Pr\{X_n = k\} = \frac{1}{4},k=0,1,2,3 $ for all $ n $, where $k$ is the state of the Markov chain. For $n \in \mathbb{N}$ (the set of all natural numbers), deduce a general result from this example.

Problem: 
 Suppose $ X_n $ is a two-state Markov chain whose transition probability matrix is 
  \[ 
 \mathbf{P} = 
 \begin{array}{l}
 \begin{array}{lll}
 \hspace{0.1cm} & \ \ \ \ \ 0 \ & \  \  \  \  \  \  1 \ \ 
 \end{array} \\
 \begin{array}{c}
 0\\
 1\\
 \end{array}
 \begin{Vmatrix}
 \alpha & 1 - \alpha   \\ 
 1 - \beta & \beta   \\ 
 \end{Vmatrix}
 \end{array}
 \]
Then, $ Z_n =(X_{n-1},X_n) $ is a Markov chain having the four states $\{0, 1, 2, 3\} = \{(0,0),(0,1), (1,0), (1,1)\}$. Determine the transition probability matrix.

fields.solutions:
\begin{align*}
\Pr\{Z_0 = (0,0) = 0\} 
&= \textbf{P}_{00} = \alpha\\
\Pr\{Z_0 = (0,1) = 1\} 
&= \textbf{P}_{01} = 1 - \alpha\\
\Pr\{Z_0 = (1,0) = 2\} 
&= \textbf{P}_{10} = 1 - \beta\\
\Pr\{Z_0 = (1,1) = 3\} 
&= \textbf{P}_{11} = \beta\\ 
\\
\Pr\{Z_1 = 0 | Z_0 = 0\} 
&= \textbf{P}'_{00} = \textbf{P}_{00}= \alpha\\
\Pr\{Z_1 = 1 | Z_0 = 0\} 
&= \textbf{P}'_{01} = \textbf{P}_{01} = 1 - \alpha\\
\Pr\{Z_1 = 2 | Z_0 = 0\} 
&= \textbf{P}'_{02} = 0 = \Pr\{Z_1 = 3 | Z_0 = 0\} = \textbf{P}_{03} \\
\end{align*}
Other transition probabilities are computed similarly, and finally the transition probability matrix is:
 \[
\mathbf{P}' = 
\begin{array}{l}
\begin{array}{lllll}
\hspace{0.075cm} & \ \ 0 \ & \hspace{0.1cm} \ \  1 \ \  & \hspace{0.1cm} \ \ \ \ 2 \ \  & \hspace{0.1cm} \  3 \  \ \ \ \\
\end{array}\\
\begin{array}{c}
0\\
1\\
2\\
3\\
\end{array}
\begin{Vmatrix}
\alpha & 1 - \alpha & 0 & 0  \\ 
0 & 0 & 1 - \beta & \beta \\ 
\alpha & 1 - \alpha & 0 & 0  \\ 
0 & 0 & 1 - \beta & \beta \\ 
\end{Vmatrix}
\end{array}
\]

\[\Pr\{X_0 = 0\} = \frac{1}{8}, \Pr\{X_0 = 1\} = \frac{3}{8}, \Pr\{X_0 = 2\} = \frac{3}{8}, \Pr\{X_0 = 3\} = \frac{1}{8} \]

If 0 head appears in the previous toss, then 3 tails must appear in this toss:
\begin{align*}
\rightarrow \Pr\{X_1 = 0| X_0 = 0\} 
&= \Pr\{X_1 = 1| X_0 = 0\} = \Pr\{X_1 = 2| X_0 = 0\} = 0\\
\Pr\{X_1 = 3| X_0 = 0\} 
&= 1\\
\end{align*}
If 1 head appears in the previous toss, then 2 or 3 tails will appear in this toss where both probabilities are 1/2 :
\begin{align*}
\rightarrow \Pr\{X_1 = 2| X_0 = 1\} 
&= \frac{1}{2} = \Pr\{X_1 = 3| X_0 = 1\} \\
\Pr\{X_1 = 0| X_0 = 1\} 
&= 0 = \Pr\{X_1 = 1| X_0 = 1\} \\
\end{align*}
If 2 head appear in the previous toss, then 1, 2 or 3 tail(s) will appear in this toss where the corresponding probabilities are 1/4, 1/2 and 1/4 respectively :
\begin{align*}
\rightarrow \Pr\{X_1 = 3| X_0 = 2\} 
&= \frac{1}{4} = \Pr\{X_1 = 1| X_0 = 2\}\\
\Pr\{X_1 = 2| X_0 = 2\}  
&= \frac{1}{2} \\
\Pr\{X_1 = 0| X_0 = 2\} 
&= 0  \\
\end{align*}
If 3 head appear in the previous toss, then 0, 1, 2 or 3 tail(s) will appear in this toss where the corresponding probabilities are 1/8, 3/8, 3/8 and 1/8 respectively :
\begin{align*}
\rightarrow \Pr\{X_1 = 3| X_0 = 3\} 
&= \frac{1}{8} = \Pr\{X_1 = 0| X_0 = 3\} \\
\Pr\{X_1 = 2| X_0 = 3\} 
&= \frac{3}{8} = \Pr\{X_1 = 1| X_0 = 3\} 
\end{align*}
the transition probability matrix is:
 \[
 \mathbf{P} = 
 \begin{array}{l}
 \begin{array}{lllll}
 \hspace{0.125cm} & \ \  \ 0 \ & \hspace{0.125cm} \ \ 1 \ \  & \hspace{0.125cm}  \ 2 \ \  & \hspace{0.125cm} \  3 \  \ \ \ \\
 \end{array}\\
\begin{array}{c}
0\\
1\\
2\\
3\\
\end{array}
\begin{Vmatrix}
  0 & 0 & 0 & 1  \\ 
  0 & 0 & 1/2 & 1/2 \\ 
  0 & 1/4 & 1/2 & 1/4  \\ 
  1/8 & 3/8 & 3/8 & 1/8 \\ 
\end{Vmatrix}
 \end{array}
 \]

If a head appears in the this toss and no head appeared in the previous toss, then it will become state 1; otherwise it returns to state 0:
\begin{align*}
\rightarrow \Pr\{X_1 = 0| X_0 = 0\} 
&= \frac{1}{2} = \Pr\{X_1 = 1| X_0 = 0\} \\
\Pr\{X_1 = 2| X_0 = 0\} 
&= 0 = \Pr\{X_1 = 3| X_0 = 0\} \\
\end{align*}
If a head appears in this toss and one head appeared in the previous toss, then it will become state 2; otherwise it returns to state 0:
\begin{align*}
\rightarrow \Pr\{X_1 = 0| X_0 = 1\} 
&= \frac{1}{2} = \Pr\{X_1 = 2| X_0 = 1\} \\
\Pr\{X_1 = 1| X_0 = 1\} 
&= 0 = \Pr\{X_1 = 3| X_0 = 1\} \\
\end{align*}
If a tail appears in this toss and two heads appeared in the last two tosses, then it will become state 3; otherwise it returns to state 0:
\begin{align*}
\rightarrow \Pr\{X_1 = 0| X_0 = 2\} 
&= \frac{1}{2} = \Pr\{X_1 = 3| X_0 = 2\} \\
\Pr\{X_1 = 1| X_0 = 2\} 
&= 0 = \Pr\{X_1 = 2| X_0 = 2\} \\
\end{align*}
If it is at state 3, you win the game which means you stay at state 3:
\begin{align*}
\rightarrow \Pr\{X_1 = 3| X_0 = 3\} 
&= 1  \\
\Pr\{X_1 = 0| X_0 = 3\} 
&= 0 = \Pr\{X_1 = 1| X_0 = 3\}  = \Pr\{X_1 = 2| X_0 = 3\}
\end{align*}
the transition probability matrix is:
 \[
 \mathbf{P} = 
 \begin{array}{l}
 \begin{array}{lllll}
 \hspace{0.125cm} & \ \  \ 0 \ & \hspace{0.125cm} \ \ 1 \ \  & \hspace{0.1cm}  \ 2 \ \  & \hspace{0.125cm} \  3 \  \ \ \ \\
 \end{array}\\
\begin{array}{c}
0\\
1\\
2\\
3\\
\end{array}
\begin{Vmatrix}
  1/2 & 1/2 & 0 & 0  \\ 
  1/2 & 0 & 1/2 & 0 \\ 
  1/2 & 0 & 0 & 1/2  \\ 
  0 & 0 & 0 & 1 \\ 
\end{Vmatrix}
